abstract: The parent of Facebook, Instagram and WhatsApp reduced its work force by 13 percent and extended a hiring freeze through the first quarter of next year.
snippet: The parent of Facebook, Instagram and WhatsApp reduced its work force by 13 percent and extended a hiring freeze through the first quarter of next year.
lead_paragraph: Since Mark Zuckerberg founded Facebook in 2004, the Silicon Valley company has steadily hired more employees. At the end of September, it had amassed its largest-ever number of workers, totaling 87,314 people.

main: Meta Lays Off More Than 11,000 Employees
print_headline: After Growing Too Quickly, Meta Cuts 13% of Workers

abstract: Part public housing for fish, part carbon-capture project, part art installation, Ximena Caminoss project for Miami Beach, known as the ReefLine, aims to call attention to the challenges facing the citys marine life.
snippet: Part public housing for fish, part carbon-capture project, part art installation, Ximena Caminoss project for Miami Beach, known as the ReefLine, aims to call attention to the challenges facing the citys marine life.
lead_paragraph: New York has the High Line, Miami has the Underline and, in the next few years, Miami Beach will have the ReefLine  a monumental public work featuring an art-studded underwater sculpture park, a carbon-sequestering artificial reef and a seven-mile snorkel trail running from Fourth Street in South Beach to Bal Harbour.

main: Meet the Woman Planning an Underwater Highline
print_headline: Meet the Woman Planning An Underwater High Line To Help Protect Marine Life

lead_paragraph: Bola Tinubu, a former state governor and a powerful political kingmaker in Nigeria, was declared the West African nations next president yesterday after a closely fought contest. abstract: The Times critics Dwight Garner and Jason Zinoman celebrate the life and work of the great British novelist and literary critic, who died last week.
snippet: The Times critics Dwight Garner and Jason Zinoman celebrate the life and work of the great British novelist and literary critic, who died last week.
lead_paragraph: The writer Martin Amis, who died last week at the age of 73, was a towering figure of English literature. Practically born into the limelight, as the son of the celebrated British novelist Kingsley Amis, he secured his own fame in 1973 with the publication of his novel The Rachel Papers, and for the next half century went on to produce a scintillating body of ambitious, raucous, witty and stylish works of fiction and literary journalism distinguished by their cutting intelligence and virtuosic prose.

abstract: A mother lost her daughter 40 years ago. Until investigators knocked on her door, she had no idea what had happened.
snippet: A mother lost her daughter 40 years ago. Until investigators knocked on her door, she had no idea what had happened.
lead_paragraph: Cecile Gaspar wasnt home when the men first showed up. It was mid-October 2020, and she and her husband, Warren, were spending the day with a grandniece, their weekly babysitting engagement. But she caught a glimpse of the visitors through her doorbell camera and, noticing their tucked-in shirts, she shrugged them off as Mormon missionaries. They came by again while she was out.

main: The Young Woman Behind a Last Mystery of the Green River Killer
